Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of connected surgical robotics and the privacy challenges that arise from it. This topic falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). The paper also discusses the shift in the threat model and the basic unit of privacy control, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the role of surgeons and the hospital system, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the need for rigorous specification and verification of contextual privacy policies, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
